author: Mike Santa Barbara
title: Milford downs Laurel 52-14
text: Comment By Mike Santa Barbara Posted Oct. 23, 2015 @ 11:05 pm After suffering just their second defeat of the year last week against Indian River, Milford bounced back on Friday night, defeating Laurel 52-14. Leading by just two, 16-14, at the half the Buccaneers offense went to work in the second half scoring 36 second half points to run away with the double-digit victory. The Bucs are now 5-2 on the year, and 2-1 within the division. They’re back in action next night hosting Woodbridge in the school’s Breast Cancer Awareness game starting at 7:30 p.m.
